<h1>My Journey</h1>

<h2>June</h2>
<p>
In June, I learned about the URL and the World Wide Web. I understood how websites are 
connected on the internet and how a URL helps users find a specific webpage online.
</p>

<h2>August</h2>
<p>
In August, I learned about HTML tags and HTML links. HTML tags are used to create the 
structure of a webpage, while links allow users to connect and move from one page to another.
</p>

<h2>September</h2>
<p>
In September, I learned how to create HTML tables. Tables help organize information 
into rows and columns, making data easier to read and understand.
</p>

<h2>October</h2>
<p>
In October, I learned how to create a login box and use different input types. 
These are used in forms where users can enter information like usernames and passwords.
</p>

<h2>November</h2>
<p>
In November, I learned about website planning and website sections. I learned how 
to organize a website into different parts like Home, About, Educational, and Journey.
</p>

<h2>December</h2>
<p>
In December, I learned about multimedia in websites. This includes adding images, 
videos, and audio to make webpages more interactive and interesting.
</p>

<h2>January</h2>
<p>
In January, I learned about form elements and HTML input types. These allow users 
to submit information through forms on a webpage.
</p>

<h2>February</h2>
<p>
In February, I started learning CSS and the basic pattern of CSS. CSS is used to 
design and style a webpage by changing colors, layouts, and fonts.
</p>

<h2>March</h2>
<p>
In March, I learned about CSS fonts and colors. This helped me improve the appearance 
of my website and make it look more attractive and professional.
</p>
